parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Hydraulic Emergency Back-up Brake System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic emergency back-up brake system can cause the warning lights, buzzer, and electric motor to malfunction, leading to potential brake failure, accidents, or electrical system damage.
symptoms: The hydraulic emergency back-up brake system warning lights
buzzer
and electric motor come on intermittently
even when the main braking system is fully operational; the electrical back-up brake system runs even when the car is off
causing problems with wiring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to complete recall repairs in a timely manner can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealerships refusing to perform recall repairs
lack of communication from service centers
delayed scheduling of repairs
unnecessary forms and procedures required before repairs can be scheduled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose fan mountings can cause the fan to come loose and potentially damage other engine components, leading to engine failure or accidents.
symptoms: Fan mountings do not stay flush with engine brackets
pulleys are not adequate
noise or vibration from the engine area
overheating engine
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle shaft can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected brake lock-up
difficulty stopping the vehicle
unusual noises or vibrations from the wheels or brakes
visible signs of axle shaft damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shock mounting bolts can cause the shock absorbers to become loose, leading to reduced vehicle stability, compromised handling, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Unusual noises or clunking sounds from the suspension
uneven tire wear
reduced vehicle stability
vibration while driving
loose or broken shock mounting bolts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty throttle cable can cause the throttle to stick or malfunction, leading to unexpected acceleration or deceleration, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The throttle pedal sticks or is hard to press
the engine RPM surges or drops unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates suddenly
the throttle pedal has a rough or binding feel.
